arXiv:2411.03238v1 Announce Type: new Abstract: In this work, we analyze the new physics effects in semileptonic decay $ ar{B_s} 	o K^{*+}(	o K\pi) \ell^-  ar{
u}_\ell$ induced by the $b 	o u \ell 
u_{\ell}$ quark level transition. We consider the vector, axial vector, scalar, pseudoscalar and tensor new physics Lorentz structures in addition to the SM in effective field theory approach. New physics wilson coefficients are contrained by the available experimental measurements of leptonic and semileptonic decays of $B$ mesons induced by the same quark level transition $b 	o u \ell 
u_{\ell}$. We explore the new physics effects in differential branching fraction, lepton forward-backward asymmetry and longitudinal polarization fraction of $K^*$ meson in $ ar{B_s} 	o K^{*+}(	o K\pi) \ell^-  ar{
u}_\ell$ decay. In addition, we also provide the predictions for the integrated values of normalized angular obseravbles in different new physics scenarios.

arXiv:2408.13776v2 Announce Type: replace Abstract: We study the exclusive semileptonic decays $\Upsilon(1S)	o B_{(c)}\ell ar{
u}_\ell$, where $\ell = e,\mu,	au$. The relevant hadronic form factors are calculated using the Covariant Confined Quark Model developed previously by our group. We predict the branching fractions $\mathcal{B}(\Upsilon(1S)	o B_{(c)}\ell ar{
u}_\ell)$ to be of the order of $10^{-13}$ and $10^{-10}$ for the case of $B$ and $B_c$, respectively. Our predictions agree well with other theoretical calculations. We also consider the effects of possible New Physics in the case of $\Upsilon(1S)	o B_c	au ar{
u}_	au$. We show that the branching fraction of this decay can be enhanced by an order of magnitude using constraints from the $B	o D^{(*)}\ell ar{
u}_\ell$ and $B_c	o J/\psi\ell  ar{
u}_\ell$ experimental data.
